  "text": "Blair fusion used to be adapted for this condition because it uses the healthy talar neck. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Although minimal discrepancy of the lower leg remains after this procedure, hindfoot instability and non union in the fixation site sometimes occurred. In some cases, iliac crest harvest and external fixator may be necessary.",
